    56	<!-- ANCHOR:phase-context -->
    57	## Phase Context
    58	
    59	This is **Phase 10** of the deep-agent-improvement model-benchmark mode decomposition.
    60	
    61	**Scope Boundary**: Only the `references/` and `assets/` trees of the deep-agent-improvement skill plus the path literals inside SKILL.md and the skill graph-metadata. Scripts stay where they are (phase 013 owns the script reorg).
    62	
    63	**Dependencies**:
    64	- 009-skill-md-two-lane shipped the two co-equal lane structure in prose, so the disk layout can now mirror it.
    65	
    66	**Deliverables**:
    67	- references/ regrouped into agent-improvement, model-benchmark, shared subdirs
    68	- assets/ regrouped into the same three lane subdirs
    69	- SKILL.md path literals repointed to the new lane paths
    70	- graph-metadata refreshed for the moved files
    71	<!-- /ANCHOR:phase-context -->
    72	
    73	---
    74	
    75	<!-- ANCHOR:problem -->
    76	## 2. PROBLEM & PURPOSE
    77	
    78	### Problem Statement
    79	The skill now has two co-equal lanes (agent-improvement and model-benchmark) in its prose, but `references/` and `assets/` are still function-organized (integration, promotion-gates, scoring, workflow). A reader cannot tell which lane a doc serves by looking at the tree, and the lane boundary lives only in SKILL.md narrative.
    80	
    81	### Purpose
    82	Make the two-lane split visible on disk by physically grouping references and assets into agent-improvement, model-benchmark, and shared subdirs, with every SKILL path literal repointed.
    83	<!-- /ANCHOR:problem -->
    84	
    85	---
    86	
    87	<!-- ANCHOR:scope -->
    88	## 3. SCOPE
    89	
    90	### In Scope
    91	- Move the 14 references docs into `references/{agent-improvement,model-benchmark,shared}/`
    92	- Move the assets into `assets/{agent-improvement,model-benchmark,shared}/`
    93	- Rewrite every references/ and assets/ path literal in SKILL.md
    94	- Refresh the skill graph-metadata for the moved file paths
    95	
    96	### Out of Scope
    97	- The `scripts/` tree - phase 013 owns the physical script reorg
    98	- Editing doc bodies - this phase only moves files and repoints literals, no content rewrites
    99	
   100	### Files to Change
   101	
   102	| File Path | Change Type | Description |
   103	|-----------|-------------|-------------|
   104	| `.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/references/**` | Move | 14 docs into three lane subdirs |
   105	| `.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/assets/**` | Move | runtime + benchmark assets into three lane subdirs |
   106	| `.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/SKILL.md` | Modify | repoint all references/ and assets/ path literals |
   107	| `.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/graph-metadata.json` | Modify | refresh moved file paths if listed |
   108	<!-- /ANCHOR:scope -->
   109	
   110	---
   111	
   112	<!-- ANCHOR:requirements -->
   113	## 4. REQUIREMENTS
   114	
   115	### P0 - Blockers (MUST complete)
   116	
   117	| ID | Requirement | Acceptance Criteria |
   118	|----|-------------|---------------------|
   119	| REQ-001 | references/ split into three lane subdirs | `references/agent-improvement/`, `references/model-benchmark/`, `references/shared/` each hold their mapped docs with no doc left in a function dir |
   120	| REQ-002 | assets/ split into three lane subdirs | `assets/agent-improvement/`, `assets/model-benchmark/`, `assets/shared/` hold their mapped assets and benchmark assets land in model-benchmark |
   121	| REQ-003 | SKILL.md path literals repointed | `rg "references/(integration|promotion-gates|scoring|workflow)/" SKILL.md` returns nothing and `rg "assets/(benchmark-|improvement_|target_)" SKILL.md` returns nothing |
   122	
   123	### P1 - Required (complete OR user-approved deferral)
   124	
   125	| ID | Requirement | Acceptance Criteria |
   126	|----|-------------|---------------------|
   127	| REQ-004 | skill graph-metadata refreshed | moved file paths in `graph-metadata.json` match the new lane paths |
   128	<!-- /ANCHOR:requirements -->
   129	
