.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/004-validation-and-docs/spec.md:27:**Parent:** `122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode`
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/004-validation-and-docs/spec.md:35:Bring all documentation and metadata up to the three-lane (A: agent-improvement, B: model-benchmark, C: skill-benchmark) reality of the renamed `deep-improvement` skill, and run the hardening/deep-review gate.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/004-validation-and-docs/spec.md:39:- `deep-improvement/SKILL.md`: two-lane → three-lane (WHEN-TO-USE table, smart-router intents/RESOURCE_MAP for `skill-benchmark`, lane-aware references/assets, integration points).
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/004-validation-and-docs/spec.md:40:- `README.md` + skill catalog/playbook/advisor labels: add Lane C.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/004-validation-and-docs/spec.md:41:- `descriptions.json` + skill-advisor graph: reflect Lane C command + skill name.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/004-validation-and-docs/spec.md:43:- Hardening/deep-review: run `/deep:start-review-loop` (or equivalent) over the new Lane C code; fix findings.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/004-validation-and-docs/spec.md:48:- Advisor rebuild + validate green; Lane C discoverable via advisor.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/spec.md:2:title: "Feature Specification: deep-improvement — skill-benchmark mode + rename"
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/spec.md:3:description: "Phase parent: rename deep-agent-improvement to deep-improvement and add Lane C (skill-benchmark) measuring a skill's real-world routing, unprompted reference/asset discovery, efficiency, and usefulness; multi-model deep research (001) informs rename (002), Lane C build (003), and validation/docs (004)."
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/spec.md:5:  - "122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode"
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/spec.md:6:  - "skill-benchmark mode"
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/spec.md:7:  - "deep-improvement skill rename"
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/spec.md:12:    packet_pointer: "skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode"
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/spec.md:16:    next_safe_action: "Run multi-model deep research in 001-skill-benchmark-deep-research"
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/spec.md:26:# Spec 122 — deep-improvement: skill-benchmark mode + skill rename
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/spec.md:37:Evolve the `deep-agent-improvement` skill into a broader **`deep-improvement`** evaluation skill and add a third evaluation lane that benchmarks *skills themselves*.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/spec.md:41:1. **Rename `deep-agent-improvement` → `deep-improvement`.** The skill no longer only improves agent `.md` files. It already carries Lane A (agent-improvement) and Lane B (model-benchmark), and this packet adds Lane C (skill-benchmark). The `-agent-` infix in the name is now too narrow and miscommunicates scope.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/spec.md:43:2. **Add Lane C — skill-benchmark mode.** A new evaluation lane that measures whether a *skill* is actually well-structured, well-routed, efficient, and useful **in practice** — i.e. how real AI agents discover and use it in situ — and emits actionable findings that a follow-up packet can remediate.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/spec.md:51:`deep-agent-improvement` (evaluator-first bounded improvement) currently ships:
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/spec.md:54:- **Lane B — model-benchmark** (`/deep:start-model-benchmark-loop`): benchmark a model or prompt framework against repeatable fixtures; pattern or 5-dim scoring; deterministic or graded runs. Built across packet **121** (`121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode`).
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/spec.md:55:- **Three pluggable seams** shared by all lanes: candidate-source, dispatcher, scorer. Entry: `scripts/shared/loop-host.cjs --mode=<lane>`. References/assets/scripts are organized by lane (`agent-improvement/`, `model-benchmark/`, `shared/`).
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/spec.md:58:Lane C is the natural third lane: same loop shape, same three seams, a new fixture/dispatcher/scorer triple scoped to *skills*.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/spec.md:79:- **G1.** Rename `deep-agent-improvement` → `deep-improvement` across every surface (skill dir, `SKILL.md`, commands, agent + runtime mirrors, skill-advisor graph, `descriptions.json`, and all cross-references) with zero dangling references and a green skill-advisor rebuild.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/spec.md:80:- **G2.** Define Lane C ("skill-benchmark") precisely: what it measures, the fixture (scenario) schema, the unprompted-dispatch capture method, the scoring dimensions, and the remediation-report format.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/spec.md:81:- **G3.** Implement Lane C as a third lane reusing the candidate/dispatcher/scorer seams and `loop-host.cjs --mode=skill-benchmark`, with a `/deep:start-skill-benchmark-loop` command.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/spec.md:83:- **G5.** Keep Lane A and Lane B byte-identical when no `--mode=skill-benchmark` flag is set (no regression to existing lanes).
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/spec.md:88:- **NG1.** Actually *remediating* the skills that Lane C flags (Lane C is diagnostic; remediation is separate, optionally via Lane A).
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/spec.md:89:- **NG2.** Replacing `sk-doc` doc-shape validation or the existing manual testing playbooks — Lane C is complementary, not a replacement.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/spec.md:97:**In scope:** the `deep-improvement` skill (post-rename), its commands/agent/mirrors, advisor metadata, and the new Lane C surface (references/assets/scripts under a `skill-benchmark/` domain), plus the deep-research that informs the design.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/spec.md:99:**Out of scope:** changes to skills *other than* as benchmark *targets* of Lane C; changes to `deep-loop-runtime` internals; changes to `deep-review`/`deep-research` workflows beyond consuming them.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/spec.md:111:| **001** | `001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/` | 20-iteration deep-research loop investigating Lane C design (what to measure, how to capture unprompted routing/discovery, scoring, remediation) **and** the rename impact map. Multi-model: 5× MiniMax-2.7, 5× DeepSeek-v4-pro, 5× GPT-5.5 (xhigh, fast), 5× Opus-4.8 native. | — |
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/spec.md:112:| **002** | `002-skill-rename-deep-improvement/` | Rename `deep-agent-improvement` → `deep-improvement` across all surfaces; advisor rebuild; no dangling refs. | 001 (impact map) |
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/spec.md:113:| **003** | `003-skill-benchmark-mode/` | Design + build Lane C in the renamed skill: scenario fixtures, unprompted dispatcher, routing/discovery/efficiency/usefulness scorer, report, `/deep:start-skill-benchmark-loop`. | 001, 002 |
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/spec.md:120:## 7. Lane C — requirements (to be confirmed/refined by Phase 001 research)
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/spec.md:122:Working hypothesis for what Lane C measures. Phase 001 deep research validates, corrects, and operationalizes these; Phase 003 implements the converged design.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/spec.md:124:- **R1 — Routing/activation accuracy.** Given a realistic prompt that *should* activate the target skill at a specific intent, does the skill-advisor + the skill's smart router select the right skill and the right intent/resource set? Measure precision/recall over a scenario suite (including near-miss negatives that should *not* activate).
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/spec.md:126:- **R3 — Efficiency / bottlenecks.** Tool-calls and token cost to reach the needed resource; over-loading (too much context), under-loading (missing needed refs), ambiguous routing keys, fallback misfires, dead-ends.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/spec.md:133:- **Fixtures** = a scenario set per target skill: realistic prompt + expected activation + expected resource(s) + correct-outcome rubric, including negatives.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/spec.md:134:- **Dispatcher** = run each scenario against an executor in a *hint-free* harness, capturing the resource-load trace and tool trace (what it opened, in what order, how many calls).
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/spec.md:135:- **Scorer** = compare actual vs expected across R1–R5 → skill-benchmark dimensions; emit R6 report. Reuses the deterministic-checks + pluggable-grader shape of the Lane B 5-dim scorer.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/spec.md:136:- **Mode** = `loop-host.cjs --mode=skill-benchmark`; every state record carries `mode: skill-benchmark`; reports carry a `scoringMethod`.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/spec.md:137:- **Promotion** = Lane C is **advisory/diagnostic** by default (emits a report; does not mutate the target skill). Optional hand-off: feed findings into Lane A to actually improve a `SKILL.md`.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/spec.md:144:- **SC2.** Rename (Phase 002) leaves zero dangling `deep-agent-improvement` references where `deep-improvement` is intended; skill-advisor rebuild + validate are green; Lane A/B commands still run.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/spec.md:145:- **SC3.** Lane C (Phase 003) runs end-to-end on at least one real target skill and emits a Skill Benchmark Report with ranked, actionable bottlenecks; Lane A/B behavior is unchanged when the mode flag is absent.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/spec.md:153:- **Rename blast radius.** `deep-agent-improvement` is referenced by commands, the agent + 3 runtime mirrors, the advisor graph, `descriptions.json`, the sentinel `sk-prompt-models`, and root docs. Mitigation: Phase 001 produces an exhaustive impact map before Phase 002 touches anything.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/spec.md:154:- **Lane C measurement validity.** "Did the AI find the right asset unprompted" must be measured without leaking the answer into the prompt. Mitigation: hint-free dispatch harness + held-out expected-resource keys; this is a primary research question.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/spec.md:156:- **Scope creep into remediation.** Easy to drift from "diagnose" to "fix". Mitigation: NG1 freezes Lane C as diagnostic.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/spec.md:162:- Skill under change: `.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/SKILL.md` (→ `deep-improvement`).
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/spec.md:163:- Sibling packet (Lane B, template): `.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/`.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/spec.md:172:- OQ1. Exact scoring dimensions + weights for Lane C (R1–R5) and how to normalize across skills of different shapes.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/spec.md:173:- OQ2. How to build a credible *hint-free* dispatch harness that still captures the resource-load trace.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/spec.md:177:- OQ6. Whether `/deep:start-skill-benchmark-loop` should reuse the model-benchmark command scaffold or get its own.
