.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/014-two-lane-deep-review/review/iterations/iteration-4.md:1:[{"id":"maintainability-4-1","severity":"P2","dimension":"maintainability","title":"Max-iteration binding is split","file":".opencode/commands/deep/start-model-benchmark-loop.md","line":101,"evidence":"The Default Resolution Table binds lane/profile/spec_folder/outputs_dir/execution_mode/scoring_method/grader/executor/model, but no `max_iterations`; the Lane B YAMLs still consume `{max_iterations}` via `max_repeats`.","fix":"Add `max_iterations` to the Lane B command argument-hint, Default Resolution Table, Phase Output, and status verification; bind it before loading either YAML, defaulting to 5."},{"id":"maintainability-4-2","severity":"P2","dimension":"maintainability","title":"Grader provenance is not persisted","file":".opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/model-benchmark/run-benchmark.cjs","line":371,"evidence":"`graderKind` is read from `args.grader` and passed into 5dim scoring, but the success `report` and benchmark_run JSONL row persist only `scoringMethod: scorer`, not the grader used.","fix":"Persist `grader: graderKind` in `report`, each 5dim row or report metadata, and the appended benchmark_run record; add a regression test for 5dim+mock/llm attribution."},{"id":"maintainability-4-3","severity":"P2","dimension":"maintainability","title":"Unknown modes collapse into Lane A","file":".opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/shared/reduce-state.cjs","line":614,"evidence":"The reducer computes `const mode = record.mode === 'model-benchmark' ? 'model-benchmark' : 'agent-improvement';`, so missing or misspelled modes are silently counted as agent-improvement.","fix":"Validate `record.mode` against the known lane enum; preserve an `unknown` bucket or emit an infra warning instead of attributing malformed records to Lane A."},{"id":"maintainability-4-4","severity":"P2","dimension":"maintainability","title":"Benchmark profile duplicates fixture schema","file":".opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/assets/model-benchmark/benchmark-profiles/default.json","line":7,"evidence":"The profile defines `fixtureDir` and `fixtures` at the top level, then repeats the same `fixtureDir` and `fixtures` under `benchmark`, creating two sources that must stay in sync.","fix":"Choose one canonical fixture declaration shape, update `run-benchmark.cjs` to read that shape, and add schema validation that rejects mismatched legacy duplicates during transition."},{"id":"maintainability-4-5","severity":"P2","dimension":"maintainability","title":"Advisor disambiguation uses alias-shaped penalty ids","file":".opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/lib/scorer/lanes/explicit.ts","line":128,"evidence":"Lane B phrase boosts push `deep-model-benchmark` while penalizing `command-spec-kit-deep-agent-improvement`; aliases.ts defines that string as an alias, not the canonical Lane A skill id used elsewhere, making the tuning hard to reason about and easy to make inert.","fix":"Normalize skill ids inside the explicit-lane scorer or use actual projection ids for both boosts and penalties; add an advisor test showing model-benchmark phrasing beats Lane A without relying on alias-only ids."}]
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/006-deep-loop-empty-archive-dir-fix/implementation-summary.md:12:    packet_pointer: "skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/006-deep-loop-empty-archive-dir-fix"
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/006-deep-loop-empty-archive-dir-fix/implementation-summary.md:43:| **Spec Folder** | 121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/006-deep-loop-empty-archive-dir-fix |
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/006-deep-loop-empty-archive-dir-fix/implementation-summary.md:53:Stopped the deep-loop commands from leaving empty `research_archive/` and `review_archive/` directories in spec packets. Root cause: the deep-research init step `step_create_directories` ran `mkdir -p … {state_paths.archive_root}` on every fresh/resume run, but the archive root is only used on a `restart` move — so it almost always stayed empty. Deep-review's init never created it (confirmed by git archaeology and an independent `openai/gpt-5.5-fast` read-only trace); its empties were historical/orphaned.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/006-deep-loop-empty-archive-dir-fix/implementation-summary.md:75:1. **Investigated** every `*_archive` creator via git archaeology and an independent read-only `openai/gpt-5.5-fast` trace, converging on the research-init eager mkdir as the live root cause (introduced in commit `537cd82d26`).
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/006-deep-loop-empty-archive-dir-fix/implementation-summary.md:112:1. **deep-agent-improvement `improvement_archive`** — analogous pattern; no live eager creator found in current init paths, but flagged as a watch item (not changed).
