.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/005-optin-5dim-scorer-and-skill-docs/spec.md:58:This is **Phase 5** of packet 121 — closing the substantive review deferral (F-P2-1/F-P2-2 from the 122 review) by making the ported 5-dimension scorer genuinely usable, and bringing the deep-agent-improvement skill docs current + sk-doc-aligned now that the model-benchmark mode exists.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/005-optin-5dim-scorer-and-skill-docs/spec.md:60:**Scope Boundary**: An opt-in `--scorer` flag in `run-benchmark.cjs` + docs. The default `pattern` path stays byte-identical. No change to the agent-improvement path.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/005-optin-5dim-scorer-and-skill-docs/spec.md:62:**Dependencies**: the 121/003 build (loop-host, dispatch-model, `scorer/`), the 122 review-report deferrals, sk-doc templates + DQI tool.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/005-optin-5dim-scorer-and-skill-docs/spec.md:64:**Deliverables**: opt-in 5-dim scorer wiring + tests; model-benchmark mode documented in SKILL.md (DQI excellent); README structure table current.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/005-optin-5dim-scorer-and-skill-docs/spec.md:76:The 122 review flagged that the ported 5-dim scorer (`score-model-variant.cjs`) was built and available but never wired into `run-benchmark.cjs` (deferral F-P2-1/F-P2-2), and the deep-agent-improvement SKILL.md did not document the model-benchmark mode at all (the whole 121/003 feature was undocumented in the skill).
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/005-optin-5dim-scorer-and-skill-docs/spec.md:79:Make the 5-dim scorer usable end-to-end as an opt-in, and bring the skill docs current and sk-doc-aligned, without regressing the default benchmark path or the agent-improvement path.
