.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/002-implementation-deep-research/research/iterations/iteration-004.md:17:### F1 — deep-agent-improvement has no `loop.cjs` — the loop IS the orchestration
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/002-implementation-deep-research/research/iterations/iteration-004.md:19:The deep-agent-improvement skill does not have a `loop.cjs`. Its "loop" is the journal-serialized orchestration via:
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/002-implementation-deep-research/research/iterations/iteration-004.md:24:The 120/003 `loop.cjs` is a synchronous imperative script that coordinates `dispatch → score → converge → mutate` in a single process. deep-agent-improvement uses a different pattern: async journal appends, separate reducer runs, and explicit promotion gating.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/002-implementation-deep-research/research/iterations/iteration-004.md:26:**Implication**: The "mode switch" for deep-agent-improvement must be implemented at the **entry point** that drives the journal-based loop (likely an `index.cjs` or `main.cjs` that doesn't yet exist), NOT inside reduce-state.cjs which is purely reactive.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/002-implementation-deep-research/research/iterations/iteration-004.md:54:- `infra_failure` — from either scorer
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/002-implementation-deep-research/research/iterations/iteration-004.md:61:### F4 — converge.cjs is absent from deep-agent-improvement — it may be promote-candidate.cjs
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/002-implementation-deep-research/research/iterations/iteration-004.md:63:No `converge.cjs` exists in `.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/`. The convergence logic for agent-improvement is in `promote-candidate.cjs` which evaluates promotion gates (weighted score threshold, benchmark pass, stability coefficient). For model-benchmark mode, convergence is the `benchmark_run` record's `recommendation` field (`benchmark-pass` vs `benchmark-fail`).
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/002-implementation-deep-research/research/iterations/iteration-004.md:65:The "converge" step in 120/003 evaluates whether a variant is the best seen so far. In deep-agent-improvement, this is done by:
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/002-implementation-deep-research/research/iterations/iteration-004.md:81:Since no such entry point script currently exists in deep-agent-improvement, the build delta must include creating it (or modifying the existing orchestration entry point).
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/002-implementation-deep-research/research/iterations/iteration-004.md:111:1. Add `mode: 'agent-improvement' | 'model-benchmark'` to every state record (both scorers)
