.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/013-scripts-physical-reorg/decision-record.md:37:## ADR-001: Lane Classification of the 16 Scripts
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/013-scripts-physical-reorg/decision-record.md:52:Phases 010-012 split references, assets, the agent note, the catalog, and the advisor by lane, but the 16 scripts plus the scorer subtree are still flat at `scripts/`. We need a classification that puts each script under the lane it actually serves, so the tree mirrors the two co-equal lanes.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/013-scripts-physical-reorg/decision-record.md:56:- The scorer subtree must move wholesale into model-benchmark so its internal relative requires (`./harness.cjs`, `../lib/cache.cjs`) stay valid.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/013-scripts-physical-reorg/decision-record.md:64:**We chose**: Three lane subdirs - agent-improvement (8 scripts), model-benchmark (2 scripts + scorer/), shared (6 scripts).
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/013-scripts-physical-reorg/decision-record.md:66:**How it works**: agent-improvement holds score-candidate, generate-profile, rollback-candidate, candidate-lineage, scan-integration, check-mirror-drift, trade-off-detector, benchmark-stability. model-benchmark holds dispatch-model, run-benchmark, and the scorer/ subtree moved as one unit. shared holds loop-host, promote-candidate, materialize-benchmark-fixtures, reduce-state, improvement-journal, mutation-coverage - scripts both lanes invoke or that orchestrate across lanes.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/013-scripts-physical-reorg/decision-record.md:100:| scorer relative requires break | M | move scorer/ wholesale so internal requires stay valid |
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/013-scripts-physical-reorg/decision-record.md:112:| 3 | **Sufficient?** | PASS | Three subdirs cover all 16 scripts plus scorer |
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/013-scripts-physical-reorg/decision-record.md:126:- scorer/ moved into model-benchmark/scorer/ as one unit.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/013-scripts-physical-reorg/decision-record.md:247:**How it works**: After moving into `scripts/model-benchmark/`, the state and assets joins gain one more `..` (or resolve from a computed skill-root anchor) so they point at the skill root again. A regression test materializes a known `improvement_config.json` and asserts dispatch-model reads the expected `modelBenchmarkConfig` values, catching any future silent fallback to `{}`.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/007-benchmark-mode-hardening-review/spec.md:3:description: "10-iteration deep review (cli-codex gpt-5.5 high/fast + cli-opencode MiniMax M2.7, alternating) of the session's authored code and docs: the deep-agent-improvement model-benchmark mode build (121/003) and the MiniMax integration (120) — correctness, security, traceability, maintainability."
