.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/references/shared/loop_protocol.md:59:- The scorer produces per-dimension scores (structural, ruleCoherence, integration, outputQuality, systemFitness)
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/references/shared/loop_protocol.md:69:- Reject if the scorer flags structure, safety, or scope issues
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/002-implementation-deep-research/research/iterations/iteration-003.md:1:# Iteration 3 — Q3: Port eval-rig scorer / 5-dim rubric
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/002-implementation-deep-research/research/iterations/iteration-003.md:4:Port the 120/003 `score-variant.cjs` (deterministic checks + claude grader harness + 5-dim rubric) into deep-agent-improvement behind the scorer seam, decoupling it from fixture-only assumptions so the same scorer works for **agent-improvement** (profile-based, 5-dim rubric) and **model-benchmark** (fixture-based, pattern matching).
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/002-implementation-deep-research/research/iterations/iteration-003.md:9:2. **Read `run-benchmark.cjs`** (deep-agent-improvement current, 364 LOC) — the benchmark-mode scoring surface. Identified it's fixture-coupled via `requiredHeadings`/`requiredPatterns`/`forbiddenPatterns` on the output text.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/002-implementation-deep-research/research/iterations/iteration-003.md:21:**Implication**: There is no shared scorer seam. The 120/003 harness and dai benchmark scoring are parallel, non-unified code paths. Bringing them under one seam requires designing the Abstraction Barrier carefully.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/002-implementation-deep-research/research/iterations/iteration-003.md:35:Fixture schema: `{ acceptance: Array<{id,type,file,pattern,expected_count?,command?,expected_exit?}> }`
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/002-implementation-deep-research/research/iterations/iteration-003.md:79:**Agent-improvement mode** uses `score-candidate.cjs` (the 5-dim rubric scorer) — NOT yet ported from 120/003.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/002-implementation-deep-research/research/iterations/iteration-003.md:117:The seam decouples by NOT passing raw fixture objects to the scorer. Instead, the loop host (or a thin adapter layer) extracts the necessary data from the fixture/profile and passes only the primitive fields the scorer needs.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/002-implementation-deep-research/research/iterations/iteration-003.md:131:// Each criterion: { id, type, file?, pattern?, command?, expected_exit? }
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/002-implementation-deep-research/research/iterations/iteration-003.md:144:For agent-improvement mode, instead of fixture JSON, the scorer receives a profile object:
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/002-implementation-deep-research/research/iterations/iteration-003.md:160:The det-check scripts (`bundle-gate.cjs`, `cwd-check.cjs`, `preplanning-regex.cjs`, `hallucination-flag.cjs`) all receive `fixturePath` as an argument and read the fixture JSON internally. This is a second-order coupling: even if the scorer seam is abstracted, the det-check scripts remain fixture-path-coupled.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/002-implementation-deep-research/research/iterations/iteration-003.md:173:1. The new scorer seam MUST default to the existing `score-candidate.cjs` behavior when mode=`agent-improvement`
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/002-implementation-deep-research/research/iterations/iteration-003.md:175:3. The mode detection should be DONE in `loop.cjs` (or `reduce-state.cjs`), NOT inside the scorer itself — the scorer receives a pre-processed `scoringMode` argument
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/002-implementation-deep-research/research/iterations/iteration-003.md:208:- The scorer NEVER reads a fixture JSON file directly — all fixture data is extracted and passed as primitives by the loop host
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/002-implementation-deep-research/research/iterations/iteration-003.md:214:- **Q3** (partial): How to decouple the scorer from fixture coupling — yes, identified 3 coupling points (acceptance criteria array, det-check scripts via fixture JSON path, grader harness fixture object). Solution: build criteria-granular pass-through from loop host; parameterize det-check scripts with explicit `cwd`; grader factory `buildGraderFn(mode)`.
