.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/manual_testing_playbook/09--model-benchmark-mode/039-criteria-exec-gate.md:76:| `../../scripts/model-benchmark/scorer/score-model-variant.cjs` | Ported 120/003 five-dimension scorer with the criteria-exec hardening gate |
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/manual_testing_playbook/09--model-benchmark-mode/039-criteria-exec-gate.md:77:| `../../scripts/model-benchmark/run-benchmark.cjs` | Benchmark runner that routes 5dim scoring through the scorer |
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/014-two-lane-deep-review/review/iterations/iteration-9.md:1:[{"id":"correctness-9-1","severity":"P1","dimension":"correctness","title":"Benchmark pass ignores failed fixtures","file":".opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/model-benchmark/run-benchmark.cjs","line":367,"evidence":"`passCount` is computed from `entry.passed`, but `recommendation` only checks `aggregateScore >= aggregateThreshold` and `results.every((entry) => entry.score >= minimumFixtureScore)`. A fixture with failureModes/`passed:false` can still produce `benchmark-pass` if its numeric score clears the thresholds.","fix":"Require `results.every((entry) => entry.passed)` in the pass predicate, or make `minimumFixtureScore` an additional condition after all fixture pass/failure gates are clean."},{"id":"correctness-9-2","severity":"P1","dimension":"correctness","title":"5dim drops fixture contract gates","file":".opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/model-benchmark/run-benchmark.cjs","line":220,"evidence":"The 5dim adapter passes only `acceptance`, `requiredHeadings`, and `requiredPatterns` into the scorer and never performs the pattern scorer's `missingHeadings`, `missingPatterns`, or `forbiddenMatches` checks; `forbiddenPatterns` is not passed at all. Its `passed` value is derived only from hard-gate and low-dimension failure modes.","fix":"Run the same required-heading, required-pattern, and forbidden-pattern checks in `scoreFixture5dim` and gate `passed` on them, or convert those fixture requirements into scorer-enforced acceptance criteria including forbidden patterns."},{"id":"correctness-9-3","severity":"P1","dimension":"correctness","title":"Unknown graders are accepted","file":".opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/model-benchmark/run-benchmark.cjs","line":328,"evidence":"The runner validates `--scorer` with `VALID_SCORERS`, but `const graderKind = args.grader || 'noop';` accepts any grader string and forwards it into 5dim scoring. The command docs declare only `noop|mock|llm`, so typos can run unintended grading behavior instead of failing setup.","fix":"Add `VALID_GRADERS = new Set(['noop','mock','llm'])`; reject unknown graders with exit 2, or warn and explicitly default to `noop` before scoring."}]
