.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/model-benchmark/scorer/deterministic/README.md:10:# deterministic: scorer deterministic checks
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/model-benchmark/scorer/deterministic/README.md:16:`deterministic/` holds the standalone check scripts the scorer spawns as subprocesses. Each script reads a fixture JSON and a model output file, then prints one JSON line with a `score` and `passed` flag. No LLM calls happen here.
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/model-benchmark/scorer/deterministic/README.md:21:- A missing output file makes a script emit `score: 0.0` and exit 0 so the scorer keeps a clean parse.
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/model-benchmark/scorer/deterministic/README.md:41:The check scripts do not import the scorer.
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/model-benchmark/scorer/deterministic/README.md:73:| Imports | Each script imports only Node builtins (`fs`, `path`, `child_process`). No cross-script or scorer imports. |
