.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/feature_catalog/02--integration-scanning/03-command-dispatch.md:10:Routes deep-agent-improvement execution from the slash command into the auto and confirm workflow assets.
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/feature_catalog/02--integration-scanning/03-command-dispatch.md:12:This feature covers the operator-facing command surface and the workflow assets that actually run the deep-agent-improvement loop.
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/feature_catalog/02--integration-scanning/03-command-dispatch.md:20:The real dispatch authority lives in the YAML assets. Both workflow files rescan integration, dispatch `@deep-agent-improvement` to write candidates, emit journal events with `improvement-journal.cjs`, and call the scoring, coverage, trade-off, and reducer helpers. Confirm mode adds approval gates around candidate generation and post-score review, while auto mode runs the same stages without those gates.
